{{en-adj|er}}

# Having a small distance from one end or edge to another, either [[horizontal]]ly or [[vertical]]ly.
# {{context|of a person}} Of comparatively little [[height]].
# Having little duration.
# {{context|followed by '''for'''}} Of a word or phrase, constituting an abbreviation (for another) or shortened form (of another).
#: ''“Phone” is '''short''' for “telephone”, and “PTO” is '''short''' for “please turn over”.''
# {{cricket|of a ball}} that bounced relatively far from the batsman
# {{cricket|of a [[fielder]] or fielding [[position]]}} relatively [[close]] to the [[batsman]]
# [[brittle]] (of pastry); see also [[shortening]], [[shortcrust]]
# [[missing]], [[deficient]]
#: ''The cashier came up '''short''' ten dollars on his morning shift.''
# Any financial investment position that is structured to be profitable if the price of the underlying security declines in the future.
#: ''I'm '''short''' General Motors because I think their sales are plunging.''

